Company Description:

Railroads transport goods and people millions of miles every day. At Progress Rail, we believe in going the distance with them. We are looking for talented and innovative team players to address the challenges of the rail industry today, ensuring success for the future. Build a long-term career with opportunities for growth and advancement as part of a vibrant network of close to 200 global locations. Our innovative team members work together to forge the bridge between ideas and success!

As a Caterpillar company, Progress Rail is an integrated rolling stock and infrastructure provider, delivering a full range of products and services to domestic and international railroad customers. Our customers enjoy one-stop shopping and comprehensive railway solutions – whether it rolls on the rail or is the rail itself. From locomotives, transit, freight cars and engines, to tracks, signals and advanced technology, we ensure customers can count on us to meet their needs.

Learn how we keep our customers rolling by following us on Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, YouTube and LinkedIn, and by visiting progressrail.com .

Education / Training:

High School diploma required;
1-3 years of technical experience with technical knowledge to install and work with applications;
BI systems experience desired.

Job Title:

BI Systems Analyst

City:

Ft. Worth

Key Job Elements:

Key Job Elements:

Supports Business Intelligence Software Systems including financial consolidation system and reporting systems;
Performs data analysis on in-house systems ranging from financial to operational and HR related systems;
Engages and interacts with business users to identify requirements and develop documents for the reporting needs of the business; engages with business users to troubleshoot and resolve reporting issues;
Develops reports for financial analysis and management reporting; creates SQL-statement-based queries to facilitate data analysis;
Diagnoses, documents and resolves software and reporting system issues identified by the business;
Works with users to address ad-hoc data analysis requests; determines proper course of action; prioritizes tasks and responsibilities to properly manage workload;
Troubleshoots data and BO application issues; fully analyzes impact and determines strategy for resolution; assists in implementation of solutions;
Manages, maintains and administers servers and workstations utilizing BI and reporting software;
Escalates top priority, production-critical issues to appropriate support staff;
Makes recommendations of perceived solutions to potential problem areas and methods for improvement;
Performs other job-related duties as assigned.

Qualifications and Experience:

Database and reporting systems experience;
Proficient with Microsoft Office (MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint);
Excellent organizational skills/attention to detail;
Well-developed analytical and problem solving skills;
Use of good judgement and good interpersonal communication skills;
Exercises confidentiality and discretion;
Ability to manage projects as assigned.

Essential and Physical Activities Functions:

Strength – Position typically involves work in a standard office environment;
Motion – Constant sitting. Occasional standing and walking;
Vision/Hearing Requirements – Constant verbal communications, including both talking and hearing;
Work Environment – Position is consistent with standard office environment;
Emotional Demands – High focus on communications and organizational skills. Requires ability to work with a team to accomplish mission success;
Safety – Position includes safety requirements consistent primarily with a standard office environment.

EEO:

Equal Opportunity Employer – Race/Color/Sex/Religion/National Origin/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity/Vets/Disabilities

Benefits:

Progress Rail offers an excellent total compensation package,* including competitive salary, paid time off for vacation and holidays, 401(k) plan with company match, medical/dental/vision/life/disability insurance and flexible spending accounts. Relocation assistance may be available for some positions.

